meta {
  name: Update Test Group
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

patch {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/siteadmin/test-groups/{{testGroupId}}
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{siteAdminToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "groupName": "Full Body Checkup (Advanced)",
    "labTestIds": ["{{siteAdminLabTestId}}"]
  }
}

docs {
  Update a test group. Auth: SiteAdmin token, requires `master-data:write`.
  All fields optional.

  **Body**
  - `groupName` — renamed; still unique among active groups → 409
    `TEST_GROUP_NAME_CONFLICT` on a clash.
  - `labTestIds` — when provided, the **entire mapping set is replaced** (old
    active mappings soft-deleted, the new set created). Same validation as create
    (must be active SITE_ADMIN templates, no duplicates). **Omit** `labTestIds`
    to leave the current mappings untouched; pass `[]` to clear all mappings.

  404 `TEST_GROUP_NOT_FOUND` if the group is missing/soft-deleted.

  **Sample response — 200**: the updated group with its (new) `labTests[]`, same
  shape as `Get Test Group`.
}
